(17, 2, '2010-09-20 13:42:41', '2010-09-20 13:42:41', '<div id="_mcePaste">Day 1 and it certainly felt a bit like being a kid on my first day at school, but I had a pretty open mind as to who or what I may discover.  The day was full of interesting conversations, different objectives and hopes for what people may get from the experience.  There were numerous talks and workshops that helped position the content and develop relationships with the new alumni.</div>\r\n<div id="_mcePaste">The talk that really stood out to me was delivered by Dr Bill Lancaster.  Bill helped me understand two things; 1) why my Mother still nags me – due to women holding the role of ‘policewoman’ in the family since the 1600’s, still apparent in my family! 2) The Bigg Market ethos and the reasons why us Geordies wear short sleeved shirts and mini skirts in the winter – all down to the prosperous times of ‘flashy lads and lasses’ from back in the shipyards and heavy industry era.</div>\r\n<div id="_mcePaste">I think the main thing that I observed that day was motivation for leadership and purpose.  All of the people I spoke to regarding purpose had a negative experience either in school or their career.  This has acted almost as a catalyst of extreme motivation to achieve something based on strong values and beliefs.  I was quite moved by the level of motivation and determination to really make a difference to the people’s lives they could affect.</div>\r\n<div id="_mcePaste">It has made me question, as to my own journey regarding what I am trying to achieve.   I have a clear direction of where I am going, but what I deem as ‘achievement’ is still a question I need to explore.  With the word ‘achievement’ like I found on the first day the meaning of words can be very different from person to person.</div>', 'Common Purpose – The Sage – Day 1 – Plotting the Course', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-5', '', '', '2010-09-20 13:42:41', '2010-09-20 13:42:41', '', 11, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/?p=17', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(13, 2, '2010-09-20 13:41:15', '2010-09-20 13:41:15', '<div id="_mcePaste">Day 1 and it certainly felt a bit like being a kid on my first day at school, but I had a pretty open mind as to who or what I may discover.  The day was full of interesting conversations, different objectives and hopes for what people may get from the experience.  There were numerous talks and workshops that helped position the content and develop relationships with the new alumni.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div id="_mcePaste">The talk that really stood out to me was delivered by Dr Bill Lancaster.  Bill helped me understand two things; 1) why my Mother still nags me – due to women holding the role of ‘policewoman’ in the family since the 1600’s, still apparent in my family! 2) The Bigg Market ethos and the reasons why us Geordies wear short sleeved shirts and mini skirts in the winter – all down to the prosperous times of ‘flashy lads and lasses’ from back in the shipyards and heavy industry era.</div>\r\n<div id="_mcePaste">I think the main thing that I observed that day was motivation for leadership and purpose.  All of the people I spoke to regarding purpose had a negative experience either in school or their career.  This has acted almost as a catalyst of extreme motivation to achieve something based on strong values and beliefs.  I was quite moved by the level of motivation and determination to really make a difference to the people’s lives they could affect.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div id="_mcePaste">It has made me question, as to my own journey regarding what I am trying to achieve.   I have a clear direction of where I am going, but what I deem as ‘achievement’ is still a question I need to explore.  With the word ‘achievement’ like I found on the first day the meaning of words can be very different from person to person.</div>\r\nCommon Purpose – The Sage – Day 1 – Plotting the CourseWednesday, February 17th, 2010Day 1 and it certainly felt a bit like being a kid on my first day at school, but I had a pretty open mind as to who or what I may discover.  The day was full of interesting conversations, different objectives and hopes for what people may get from the experience.  There were numerous talks and workshops that helped position the content and develop relationships with the new alumni.The talk that really stood out to me was delivered by Dr Bill Lancaster.  Bill helped me understand two things; 1) why my Mother still nags me – due to women holding the role of ‘policewoman’ in the family since the 1600’s, still apparent in my family! 2) The Bigg Market ethos and the reasons why us Geordies wear short sleeved shirts and mini skirts in the winter – all down to the prosperous times of ‘flashy lads and lasses’ from back in the shipyards and heavy industry era.I think the main thing that I observed that day was motivation for leadership and purpose.  All of the people I spoke to regarding purpose had a negative experience either in school or their career.  This has acted almost as a catalyst of extreme motivation to achieve something based on strong values and beliefs.  I was quite moved by the level of motivation and determination to really make a difference to the people’s lives they could affect.It has made me question, as to my own journey regarding what I am trying to achieve.   I have a clear direction of where I am going, but what I deem as ‘achievement’ is still a question I need to explore.  With the word ‘achievement’ like I found on the first day the meaning of words can be very different from person to person.', 'Common Purpose – The Sage – Day 1 – Plotting the Course', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-2', '', '', '2010-09-20 13:41:15', '2010-09-20 13:41:15', '', 11, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/?p=13', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(12, 2, '2010-09-20 13:40:40', '2010-09-20 13:40:40', '<div id="_mcePaste"></div>\n<div id="_mcePaste">Wednesday, February 17th, 2010</div>\n<div id="_mcePaste">Day 1 and it certainly felt a bit like being a kid on my first day at school, but I had a pretty open mind as to who or what I may discover.  The day was full of interesting conversations, different objectives and hopes for what people may get from the experience.  There were numerous talks and workshops that helped position the content and develop relationships with the new alumni.</div>\n<div id="_mcePaste">The talk that really stood out to me was delivered by Dr Bill Lancaster.  Bill helped me understand two things; 1) why my Mother still nags me – due to women holding the role of ‘policewoman’ in the family since the 1600’s, still apparent in my family! 2) The Bigg Market ethos and the reasons why us Geordies wear short sleeved shirts and mini skirts in the winter – all down to the prosperous times of ‘flashy lads and lasses’ from back in the shipyards and heavy industry era.</div>\n<div id="_mcePaste">I think the main thing that I observed that day was motivation for leadership and purpose.  All of the people I spoke to regarding purpose had a negative experience either in school or their career.  This has acted almost as a catalyst of extreme motivation to achieve something based on strong values and beliefs.  I was quite moved by the level of motivation and determination to really make a difference to the people’s lives they could affect.</div>\n<div id="_mcePaste">It has made me question, as to my own journey regarding what I am trying to achieve.   I have a clear direction of where I am going, but what I deem as ‘achievement’ is still a question I need to explore.  With the word ‘achievement’ like I found on the first day the meaning of words can be very different from person to person.</div>\nCommon Purpose – The Sage – Day 1 – Plotting the CourseWednesday, February 17th, 2010Day 1 and it certainly felt a bit like being a kid on my first day at school, but I had a pretty open mind as to who or what I may discover.  The day was full of interesting conversations, different objectives and hopes for what people may get from the experience.  There were numerous talks and workshops that helped position the content and develop relationships with the new alumni.The talk that really stood out to me was delivered by Dr Bill Lancaster.  Bill helped me understand two things; 1) why my Mother still nags me – due to women holding the role of ‘policewoman’ in the family since the 1600’s, still apparent in my family! 2) The Bigg Market ethos and the reasons why us Geordies wear short sleeved shirts and mini skirts in the winter – all down to the prosperous times of ‘flashy lads and lasses’ from back in the shipyards and heavy industry era.I think the main thing that I observed that day was motivation for leadership and purpose.  All of the people I spoke to regarding purpose had a negative experience either in school or their career.  This has acted almost as a catalyst of extreme motivation to achieve something based on strong values and beliefs.  I was quite moved by the level of motivation and determination to really make a difference to the people’s lives they could affect.It has made me question, as to my own journey regarding what I am trying to achieve.   I have a clear direction of where I am going, but what I deem as ‘achievement’ is still a question I need to explore.  With the word ‘achievement’ like I found on the first day the meaning of words can be very different from person to person.', 'Common Purpose – The Sage – Day 1 – Plotting the Course', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision', '', '', '2010-09-20 13:40:40', '2010-09-20 13:40:40', '', 11, 'http://www.sherpabusinessconsultancy.com/wordpress/?p=12', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
